    "Data in Scikit-learn \n",
    "\n",
    "An observation is a vector of n features \n",
    "\n",
    "A model make a function from an input features of observation to a vector of output target values\n",
    "\n",

    "\n",

    "    Each observation contains n_features and a target value\n",

    "# load an dataset\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import load_iris\n",
    "iris = load_iris()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"data.shape:{iris.data.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"target.shape:{iris.target.shape}\")\n",

   "cell_type": "markdown",

    "id": "lRkCLY1gyD27"
   },
   "source": [
    "Scikit-learn has a very straightforward set of data on these iris species. The data consist of the following:\n",
    "\n",
    "**Features in the Iris dataset:**\n",
    "\n",
    "*   sepal length in cm\n",
    "*   sepal width in cm\n",
    "*   petal length in cm\n",
    "*   petal width in cm\n",
    "\n",
    "**Target value to predict:**\n",
    "\n",
    "*   Iris Setosa\n",
    "*   Iris Versicolour\n",
    "*   Iris Virginica"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "zC9EfqjKwuU9"
   },
   "source": [
    "<img src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/3500/1*f6KbPXwksAliMIsibFyGJw.png\" width=600 height=600 />"

   "source": [
    "<div style=\"border: solid 3px #000;\">\n",
    "    <h1 style=\"text-align: center; color:#000; font-family:Georgia; font-size:26px;\">Question</h1>\n",
    "    <h1 style=\"text-align: left; color:#000; font-family:Georgia; font-size:18px;\"> &emsp; 1. Is Iris dataset collected to model a classification problem or regression problem?</h1>\n",
    "    <h1 style=\"text-align: left; color:#000; font-family:Georgia; font-size:18px;\"> &emsp;  2. What is the meaning of data[0]=[5.1, 3.5, 1.4, 0.2] and target[0]=[0]?</h1>\n",
    "    <p style='text-align: left;'> </p>\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<div style=\"border: solid 3px #000;\">\n",
    "    <h1 style=\"text-align: center; color:#000; font-family:Georgia; font-size:26px;\">Answer</h1>\n",
    "    <h1 style=\"text-align: left; color:#000; font-family:Georgia; font-size:18px;\"> &emsp; 1. Classification. Since the output of a given sample will be a label of iris types.</h1>\n",
    "    <h1 style=\"text-align: left; color:#000; font-family:Georgia; font-size:18px;\"> &emsp;  2. It means the first sample in data has sepal length of 5.1 cm, sepal width of 3.5 cm, petal length of 1.4 cm, petal width of 0.2 cm which is the type of 0 (Iris Setosa)</h1>\n",
    "    <p style='text-align: left;'> </p>\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },

    "# K-Fold Cross Validation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "eex8bmFPVvmN"
   },
   "source": [
    "<img src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0*XbT0SzeEgmA9peG-.png\" width=600 height=600 />"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<div style=\"border: solid 3px #000;\">\n",
    "    <h1 style=\"text-align: center; color:#000; font-family:Georgia; font-size:26px;\">Exercise</h1>\n",
    "    <h1 style=\"text-align: left; color:#000; font-family:Georgia; font-size:18px;\"> &emsp; Devide the iris Data set into 5 fold and count the number of each class in each fold ...</h1>\n",
    "    <p style='text-align: left;'> </p>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Fold 0 number of samples in x_train : 120 and in y_train : 120\n",
      "\tnumber of samples in x_test : 30 and in y_test : 30\n",
      "Fold 1 number of samples in x_train : 120 and in y_train : 120\n",
      "\tnumber of samples in x_test : 30 and in y_test : 30\n",
      "Fold 2 number of samples in x_train : 120 and in y_train : 120\n",
      "\tnumber of samples in x_test : 30 and in y_test : 30\n",
      "Fold 3 number of samples in x_train : 120 and in y_train : 120\n",
      "\tnumber of samples in x_test : 30 and in y_test : 30\n",
      "Fold 4 number of samples in x_train : 120 and in y_train : 120\n",
      "\tnumber of samples in x_test : 30 and in y_test : 30\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Sulotion ...\n",
    "import random \n",
    "\n",
    "data_index_list = list(range(len(iris.data)))\n",
    "random.shuffle(data_index_list)\n",
    "number_of_folds=5\n",
    "sample_number_in_fold = int(len(data_index_list)/number_of_folds)\n",
    "\n",
    "for f in range(number_of_folds):\n",
    "    x_train=[]\n",
    "    y_train=[]\n",
    "    x_test=[]\n",
    "    y_test=[]\n",
    "    start_index_test=f*sample_number_in_fold\n",
    "    end_index_test=(f+1)*sample_number_in_fold\n",
    "    for i in range(len(data_index_list)):\n",
    "        if i>=start_index_test and i<end_index_test:\n",
    "            x_test.append(iris.data[data_index_list[i]])\n",
    "            y_test.append(iris.target[data_index_list[i]])\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            x_train.append(iris.data[data_index_list[i]])\n",
    "            y_train.append(iris.target[data_index_list[i]])\n",
    "            \n",
    "    print(f\"Fold {f} number of samples in x_train : {len(x_train)} and in y_train : {len(y_train)}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"\\tnumber of samples in x_test : {len(x_test)} and in y_test : {len(y_test)}\")\n"
   ]
  },

    "#Evaluation of classification performance of a MultiLayer Perceptron model\n",
    "from sklearn.neural_network import MLPClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import precision_score\n",

    "from sklearn.metrics import plot_precision_recall_curve\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Multi-layer Perceptron classifier\n",
    "clf_mlp = MLPClassifier(solver='sgd', activation='tanh',max_iter=2000,\n",
    "                        hidden_layer_sizes=(15,7,))\n",
    "# Train model\n",
    "clf_mlp.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",

    "target_pred = clf_mlp.predict(X_test)\n",

    "print(\"accuracy:\",accuracy_score(y_test, target_pred))\n",
    "print(\"precision:\",precision_score(y_test, target_pred))\n",
    "print(\"recall:\",recall_score(y_test, target_pred))\n",
    "print(\"f1-score:\",f1_score(y_test, target_pred))\n"

    "# 2. Write a function to calculate Root mean square error which get predicted_target_values and target_values\n",
    "def rms_error(predicted_y,y):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if len(predicted_y)!= len(y):\n",
    "        print(\"Error: The length of real target and predicted target are not the same!\")\n",
    "        return None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ms_error=0\n",
    "    for i in range(len(y)):\n",
    "        ms_error+=(predicted_y[i]-y[i])**2\n",
    "        \n",
    "    return np.sqrt(ms_error/len(y))\n",
    "        \n",
    "# 3. Split data into train and test 5 times as below and train the SVM model, compute the error (mean square error)\n",
    "test_ratio_list=[0.9,0.7,0.5,0.3,0.1]\n",
    "division_case_list=[\"1st\",\"2nd\",\"3rd\",\"4th\",\"5th\"]\n",
    "print(\"Division\\t|RMSE\\t\")\n",
    "for i in range(5):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(data_diabetes.data,\n",
    "                                                        data_diabetes.target,\n",
    "                                                        test_size=test_ratio_list[i],\n",
    "                                                        shuffle=True,\n",
    "                                                        random_state=22)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    svm_regression_model = SVR()\n",
    "    predicted_y_test = svm_regression_model.fit(X_train,y_train).predict(X_test)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    rmse=rms_error(predicted_y_test,y_test)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"{division_case_list[i]}\\t\\t|{rmse}\\t\")"
   ]
